                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d246">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">890g.01/233: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Great Britain</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Dawes</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">London</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1929-12-24T11:00:00+00:00"
                            >December 24, 1929—11 a.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received December 24—10:05 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>389. Department’s 352, December 19, 4 p.m.<note n="21" xml:id="d246fn21">Not
                        printed.</note> I have received an oral message from the Foreign Office
                    stating that Jafar Pasha is agreeable to the note contained in Department’s 317,
                    November 27, 1 p.m. The Foreign Office suggests proceeding with the signatures
                    sometime during the week, beginning January 6, to which I shall agree, failing
                    instructions to the contrary.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Dawes</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
